quran[131]{c,v,t}:
  3,93,"All food was lawful for the children of Israel, except what Israel¬†made unlawful for himself before the Torah was revealed.¬†Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúBring the Torah and read it, if your claims are true.‚ÄĚ"
  3,94,"Then whoever still fabricates lies about Allah, they will be the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  3,95,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúAllah has declared the truth. So follow the Way of Abraham, the upright‚ÄĒwho was not a polytheist.‚ÄĚ"
  3,96,Surely the first House ňĻof worshipňļ established for humanity is the one at Bakkah‚ÄĒa blessed sanctuary and a guide for ňĻallňļ people
  3,97,"In it are clear signs and the standing-place of Abraham. Whoever enters it should be safe. Pilgrimage to this House is an obligation by Allah upon whoever is able among the people.¬†And whoever disbelieves, then surely Allah is not in need of ňĻany of Hisňļ creation"
  3,98,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO People of the Book! Why do you deny the revelations of Allah, when Allah is a Witness to what you do?‚ÄĚ"
  3,99,"Say, ‚ÄúO People of the Book! Why do you turn the believers away from the Way of Allah‚ÄĒstriving to make it ňĻappearňļ crooked, while you are witnesses ňĻto its truthňļ? And Allah is never unaware of what you do.‚ÄĚ"
  3,100,"O believers! If you were to yield to a group of those who were given the Scripture, they would turn you back from belief to disbelief"
  3,101,How can you disbelieve when Allah‚Äôs revelations are recited to you and His Messenger is in your midst? Whoever holds firmly to Allah is surely guided to the Straight Path
  3,102,"O believers! Be mindful of Allah in the way He deserves,¬†and do not die except in ňĻa state of fullňļ submission ňĻto Himňļ"
  3,103,"And hold firmly to the rope of Allah¬†and do not be divided. Remember Allah‚Äôs favour upon you when you were enemies, then He united your hearts, so you‚ÄĒby His grace‚ÄĒbecame brothers. And you were at the brink of a fiery pit and He saved you from it. This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, so that you may be ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  3,104,"Let there be a group among you who call ňĻothersňļ to goodness, encourage what is good, and forbid what is evil‚ÄĒit is they who will be successful"
  3,105,And do not be like those who split ňĻinto sectsňļ and differed after clear proofs had come to them. It is they who will suffer a tremendous punishment
  3,106,"On that Day some faces will be bright while others gloomy. To the gloomy-faced it will be said, ‚ÄúDid you disbelieve after having believed? So taste the punishment for your disbelief.‚ÄĚ"
  3,107,"As for the bright-faced, they will be in Allah‚Äôs mercy, where they will remain forever"
  3,108,These are Allah‚Äôs revelations We recite to you ňĻO Prophetňļ in truth. And Allah desires no injustice to ňĻHisňļ creation
  3,109,To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And to Allah ňĻallňļ matters will be returned ňĻfor judgmentňļ
  3,110,"You are the best community ever raised for humanity‚ÄĒyou encourage good, forbid evil, and believe in Allah. Had the People of the Book believed, it would have been better for them. Some of them are faithful, but most are rebellious"
  3,111,"They can never inflict harm on you, except a little annoyance.¬†But if they meet you in battle, they will flee and they will have no helpers"
  3,112,"They will be stricken with disgrace wherever they go, unless they are protected by a covenant with Allah or a treaty with the people. They have invited the displeasure of Allah and have been branded with misery for rejecting Allah‚Äôs revelations and murdering ňĻHisňļ prophets unjustly. This is ňĻa fair rewardňļ for their disobedience and violations"
  3,113,"Yet they are not all alike: there are some among the People of the Book who are upright, who recite Allah‚Äôs revelations throughout the night, prostrating ňĻin prayerňļ"
  3,114,"They believe in Allah and the Last Day, encourage good and forbid evil, and race with one another in doing good. They are ňĻtrulyňļ among the righteous"
  3,115,They will never be denied the reward for any good they have done. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of those mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  3,116,"Indeed, neither the wealth nor children of the disbelievers will be of any benefit to them against Allah. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  3,117,"The good they do in this worldly life is like the harvest of an evil people struck by a bitter wind, destroying it ňĻcompletelyňļ. Allah never wronged them, but they wronged themselves"
  3,118,"O believers! Do not associate closely with others who would not miss a chance to harm you. Their only desire is to see you suffer. Their prejudice has become evident from what they say‚ÄĒand what their hearts hide is far worse. We have made Our revelations clear to you, if only you understood"
  3,119,"Here you are! You love them but they do not love you, and you believe in all Scriptures. When they meet you they say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ But when alone, they bite their fingertips in rage. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻMay youňļ die of your rage!‚ÄĚ Surely Allah knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  3,120,"When you ňĻbelieversňļ are touched with good, they grieve; but when you are afflicted with evil, they rejoice. ňĻYet,ňļ if you are patient and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, their schemes will not harm you in the least. Surely Allah is Fully Aware of what they do"
  3,121,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when you left your home in the early morning to position the believers in the battlefield. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,122,"ňĻRememberňļ when two groups among you ňĻbelieversňļ were about to cower, then Allah reassured them. So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  3,123,"Indeed, Allah made you victorious at Badr when you were ňĻvastlyňļ outnumbered. So be mindful of Allah, perhaps you will be grateful"
  3,124,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when you said to the believers, ‚ÄúIs it not enough that your Lord will send down a reinforcement of three thousand angels for your aid?‚ÄĚ"
  3,125,"Most certainly, if you ňĻbelieversňļ are firm and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ and the enemy launches a sudden attack on you, Allah will reinforce you with five thousand angels designated ňĻfor battleňļ"
  3,126,"Allah ordained this ňĻreinforcementňļ only as good news for you and reassurance for your hearts. And victory comes only from Allah‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise‚ÄĒ"
  3,127,"to destroy a group of the disbelievers and humble the rest, causing them to withdraw in disappointment"
  3,128,"You ňĻO Prophetňļ have no say in the matter.¬†It is up to Allah to turn to them in mercy or punish them, for indeed they are wrongdoers"
  3,129,"To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  3,130,"O believers! Do not consume interest, multiplying it many times over. And be mindful of Allah, so you may prosper"
  3,131,Guard yourselves against the Fire prepared for the disbelievers
  3,132,"Obey Allah and the Messenger, so you may be shown mercy"
  3,133,"And hasten towards forgiveness from your Lord and a Paradise as vast as the heavens and the earth, prepared for those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ"
  3,134,"ňĻThey areňļ those who donate in prosperity and adversity, control their anger, and pardon others. And Allah loves the good-doers"
  3,135,"ňĻThey areňļ those who, upon committing an evil deed or wronging themselves, remember Allah and seek forgiveness and do not knowingly persist in sin‚ÄĒand who forgives sins except Allah"
  3,136,"Their reward is forgiveness from their Lord and Gardens under which rivers flow, staying there forever. How excellent is the reward for those who work ňĻrighteousnessňļ"
  3,137,"Similar situations came to pass before you, so travel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers"
  3,138,This¬†is an insight to humanity‚ÄĒa guide and a lesson to the God-fearing
  3,139,"Do not falter or grieve, for you will have the upper hand, if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  3,140,"If you have suffered injuries ňĻat UŠł•udňļ, they suffered similarly ňĻat Badrňļ. We alternate these days ňĻof victory and defeatňļ among people so that Allah may reveal the ňĻtrueňļ believers, choose martyrs from among you‚ÄĒand Allah does not like the wrongdoers‚ÄĒ"
  3,141,and distinguish the ňĻtrueňļ believers and destroy the disbelievers
  3,142,Do you think you will enter Paradise without Allah proving which of you ňĻtrulyňļ struggled ňĻfor His causeňļ and patiently endured
  3,143,"You certainly wished ňĻfor the opportunityňļ for martyrdom before encountering it, now you have seen it with your own eyes"
  3,144,"MuŠł•ammad is no more than a messenger; other messengers have gone before him. If he were to die or to be killed, would you regress into disbelief? Those who do so will not harm Allah whatsoever. And Allah will reward those who are grateful"
  3,145,"No soul can ever die without Allah‚Äôs Will at the destined time. Those who desire worldly gain, We will let them have it, and those who desire heavenly reward, We will grant it to them. And We will reward those who are grateful"
  3,146,"ňĻImagineňļ how many devotees fought along with their prophets and never faltered despite whatever ňĻlossesňļ they suffered in the cause of Allah, nor did they weaken or give in! Allah loves those who persevere"
  3,147,"And all they said was, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Forgive our sins and excesses, make our steps firm, and grant us victory over the disbelieving people.‚ÄĚ"
  3,148,So Allah gave them the reward of this world and the excellent reward of the Hereafter. For Allah loves the good-doers
  3,149,"O believers! If you yield to the disbelievers, they will drag you back to disbelief‚ÄĒand you will become losers"
  3,150,"But no! Allah is your Guardian, and He is the best Helper"
  3,151,We will cast horror into the hearts of the disbelievers for associating ňĻfalse godsňļ with Allah‚ÄĒa practice He has never authorized. The Fire will be their home‚ÄĒwhat an evil place for the wrongdoers to stay
  3,152,"Indeed, Allah fulfilled His promise to you when you ňĻinitiallyňļ swept them away by His Will, then your courage weakened and you disputed about the command and disobeyed,¬†after Allah had brought victory within your reach. Some of you were after worldly gain while others desired a heavenly reward. He denied you victory over them as a test, yet He has pardoned you. And Allah is Gracious to the believers"
  3,153,"ňĻRememberňļ when you were running far away ňĻin panicňļ‚ÄĒnot looking at anyone‚ÄĒwhile the Messenger was calling to you from behind! So Allah rewarded your disobedience with distress upon distress. Now, do not grieve over the victory you were denied or the injury you suffered. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  3,154,"Then after distress, He sent down serenity in the form of drowsiness overcoming some of you, while others were disturbed by evil thoughts about Allah‚ÄĒthe thoughts of ňĻpre-Islamicňļ ignorance. They ask, ‚ÄúDo we have a say in the matter?‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúAll matters are destined by Allah.‚ÄĚ They conceal in their hearts what they do not reveal to you. They say ňĻto themselvesňļ, ‚ÄúIf we had any say in the matter, none of us would have come to die here.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúEven if you were to remain in your homes, those among you who were destined to be killed would have met the same fate.‚ÄĚ Through this, Allah tests what is within you and purifies what is in your hearts. And Allah knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  3,155,"Indeed, those ňĻbelieversňļ who fled on the day when the two armies met were made to slip by Satan because of their misdeeds. But Allah has pardoned them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  3,156,"O believers! Do not be like the unfaithful¬†who say about their brothers who travel throughout the land or engage in battle, ‚ÄúIf they had stayed with us, they would not have died or been killed.‚ÄĚ Allah makes such thinking a cause of agony in their hearts. It is Allah who gives life and causes death. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  3,157,"Should you be martyred or die in the cause of Allah, then His forgiveness and mercy are far better than whatever ňĻwealthňļ those ňĻwho stay behindňļ accumulate"
  3,158,Whether you die or are martyred‚ÄĒall of you will be gathered before Allah
  3,159,"It is out of Allah‚Äôs mercy that you ňĻO Prophetňļ have been lenient with them. Had you been cruel or hard-hearted, they would have certainly abandoned you. So pardon them, ask Allah‚Äôs forgiveness for them, and consult with them in ňĻconductingňļ matters. Once you make a decision, put your trust in Allah. Surely Allah loves those who trust in Him"
  3,160,"If Allah helps you, none can defeat you. But if He denies you help, then who else can help you? So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  3,161,"It is not appropriate for a prophet to illegally withhold spoils of war. And whoever does so, it will be held against them on the Day of Judgment. Then every soul will be paid in full for what it has done, and none will be wronged"
  3,162,Are those who seek Allah‚Äôs pleasure like those who deserve Allah‚Äôs wrath? Hell is their home. What an evil destination
  3,163,They ňĻeachňļ have varying degrees in the sight of Allah. And Allah is All-Seeing of what they do
  3,164,"Indeed, Allah has done the believers a ňĻgreatňļ favour by raising a messenger from among them‚ÄĒreciting to them His revelations, purifying them, and teaching them the Book and wisdom. For indeed they had previously been clearly astray"
  3,165,"Why is it when you suffered casualties ňĻat UŠł•udňļ‚ÄĒalthough you had made your enemy suffer twice as much ňĻat Badrňļ‚ÄĒyou protested, ‚ÄúHow could this be?‚ÄĚ? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIt is because of your disobedience.‚ÄĚ Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  3,166,"So what you suffered on the day the two armies met was by Allah‚Äôs Will, so that He might distinguish the ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  3,167,"and expose the hypocrites. When it was said to them, ‚ÄúCome fight in the cause of Allah or ňĻat leastňļ defend yourselves,‚ÄĚ they replied, ‚ÄúIf we had known there was fighting, we would have definitely gone with you.‚ÄĚ They were closer to disbelief than to belief on that day‚ÄĒfor saying with their mouths what was not in their hearts. Allah is All-Knowing of what they hide"
  3,168,"Those who sat at home, saying about their brothers, ‚ÄúHad they listened to us, they would not have been killed.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúTry not to die¬†if what you say is true!‚ÄĚ"
  3,169,"Never think of those martyred in the cause of Allah as dead. In fact, they are alive with their Lord, well provided for‚ÄĒ"
  3,170,"rejoicing in Allah‚Äôs bounties and being delighted for those yet to join them. There will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  3,171,"They are joyful for receiving Allah‚Äôs grace and bounty, and that Allah does not deny the reward of the believers"
  3,172,"ňĻAs forňļ those who responded to the call of Allah and His Messenger after their injury,¬†those of them who did good and were mindful ňĻof Allahňļ will have a great reward"
  3,173,"Those who were warned, ‚ÄúYour enemies have mobilized their forces against you, so fear them,‚ÄĚ the warning only made them grow stronger in faith and they replied, ‚ÄúAllah ňĻaloneňļ is sufficient ňĻas an aidňļ for us and ňĻHeňļ is the best Protector.‚ÄĚ"
  3,174,"So they returned with Allah‚Äôs favours and grace, suffering no harm. For they sought to please Allah. And surely Allah is ňĻtheňļ Lord of infinite bounty"
  3,175,"That ňĻwarningňļ was only ňĻfromňļ Satan, trying to prompt you to fear his followers.¬†So do not fear them; fear Me if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  3,176,"ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Do not grieve for those who race to disbelieve‚ÄĒsurely they will not harm Allah in the least. It is Allah‚Äôs Will to disallow them a share in the Hereafter, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  3,177,"Those who trade belief for disbelief will never harm Allah in the least, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  3,178,"Those who disbelieve should not think that living longer is good for them. They are only given more time to increase in sin, and they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  3,179,"Allah would not leave the believers in the condition you were in, until He distinguished the good from the evil ňĻamong youňļ. Nor would Allah ňĻdirectlyňļ reveal to you the unseen,¬†but He chooses whoever He wills as a messenger. So believe in Allah and His messengers. And if you are faithful and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, you will receive a great reward"
  3,180,"And do not let those who ňĻgreedilyňļ withhold Allah‚Äôs bounties think it is good for them‚ÄĒin fact, it is bad for them! They will be leashed ňĻby their necksňļ on the Day of Judgment with whatever ňĻwealthňļ they used to withhold. And Allah is the ňĻsoleňļ inheritor of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  3,181,"Indeed, Allah has heard those ňĻamong the Jewsňļ who said, ‚ÄúAllah is poor; we are rich!‚ÄĚ We have certainly recorded their slurs and their killing of prophets unjustly. Then We will say, ‚ÄúTaste the torment of burning"
  3,182,This is ňĻthe rewardňļ for what your hands have done. And Allah is never unjust to ňĻHisňļ creation.‚ÄĚ
  3,183,"Those ňĻare the same peopleňļ who say, ‚ÄúAllah has commanded us not to believe in any messenger unless he brings us an offering to be consumed by fire ňĻfrom the skyňļ.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúOther prophets did in fact come to you¬†before me with clear proofs and ňĻevenňļ what you demanded‚ÄĒwhy then did you kill them, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  3,184,"If you are rejected by them, so too were messengers before you who came with clear proofs, divine Books, and enlightening Scriptures"
  3,185,"Every soul will taste death. And you will only receive your full reward on the Day of Judgment. Whoever is spared from the Fire and is admitted into Paradise will ňĻindeedňļ triumph, whereas the life of this world is no more than the delusion of enjoyment"
  3,186,"You ňĻbelieversňļ will surely be tested in your wealth and yourselves,¬†and you will certainly hear many hurtful words from those who were given the Scripture before you and ňĻfromňļ the polytheists. But if you are patient and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ‚ÄĒsurely this is a resolve to aspire to"
  3,187,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when Allah took the covenant of those who were given the Scripture to make it known to people and not hide it, yet they cast it behind their backs and traded it for a fleeting gain. What a miserable profit"
  3,188,Do not let those who rejoice in their misdeeds and love to take credit for what they have not done think they will escape torment. They will suffer a painful punishment
  3,189,To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is Most Capable of everything
  3,190,"Indeed, in the creation of the heavens and the earth and the alternation of the day and night there are signs for people of reason"
  3,191,"ňĻThey areňļ those who remember Allah while standing, sitting, and lying on their sides, and reflect on the creation of the heavens and the earth ňĻand prayňļ, ‚ÄúOur Lord! You have not created ňĻall ofňļ this without purpose. Glory be to You! Protect us from the torment of the Fire"
  3,192,"Our Lord! Indeed, those You commit to the Fire will be ňĻcompletelyňļ disgraced! And the wrongdoers will have no helpers"
  3,193,"Our Lord! We have heard the caller¬†to ňĻtrueňļ belief, ňĻproclaiming,ňļ ‚ÄėBelieve in your Lord ňĻaloneňļ,‚Äô so we believed. Our Lord! Forgive our sins, absolve us of our misdeeds, and allow us ňĻeachňļ to die as one of the virtuous"
  3,194,Our Lord! Grant us what You have promised us through Your messengers and do not put us to shame on Judgment Day‚ÄĒfor certainly You never fail in Your promise.‚ÄĚ
  3,195,"So their Lord responded to them: ‚ÄúI will never deny any of you‚ÄĒmale or female‚ÄĒthe reward of your deeds. Both are equal in reward. Those who migrated or were expelled from their homes, and were persecuted for My sake and fought and ňĻsomeňļ were martyred‚ÄĒI will certainly forgive their sins and admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, as a reward from Allah. And with Allah is the finest reward!‚ÄĚ"
  3,196,Do not be deceived by the prosperity of the disbelievers throughout the land
  3,197,It is only a brief enjoyment. Then Hell will be their home‚ÄĒwhat an evil place to rest
  3,198,"But those who are mindful of their Lord will be in Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever‚ÄĒas an accommodation from Allah. And what is with Allah is best for the virtuous"
  3,199,"Indeed, there are some among the People of the Book who truly believe in Allah and what has been revealed to you ňĻbelieversňļ and what was revealed to them. They humble themselves before Allah‚ÄĒnever trading Allah‚Äôs revelations for a fleeting gain. Their reward is with their Lord. Surely Allah is swift in reckoning"
  3,200,"O believers! Patiently endure, persevere, stand on guard,¬†and be mindful of Allah, so you may be successful"
  4,1,"O humanity! Be mindful of your Lord Who created you from a single soul, and from it He created its mate,¬†and through both He spread countless men and women. And be mindful of Allah‚ÄĒin Whose Name you appeal to one another‚ÄĒand ňĻhonourňļ family ties. Surely Allah is ever Watchful over you"
  4,2,"Give orphans their wealth ňĻwhen they reach maturityňļ, and do not exchange your worthless possessions for their valuables, nor cheat them by mixing their wealth with your own. For this would indeed be a great sin"
  4,3,"If you fear you might fail to give orphan women their ňĻdueňļ rights ňĻif you were to marry themňļ, then marry other women of your choice‚ÄĒtwo, three, or four. But if you are afraid you will fail to maintain justice, then ňĻcontent yourselves withňļ one¬†or those ňĻbondwomenňļ in your possession.¬†This way you are less likely to commit injustice"
  4,4,"Give women ňĻyou wedňļ their due dowries graciously. But if they waive some of it willingly, then you may enjoy it freely with a clear conscience"
  4,5,"Do not entrust the incapable ňĻamong your dependantsňļ with your wealth which Allah has made a means of support for you‚ÄĒbut feed and clothe them from it, and speak to them kindly"
  4,6,"Test ňĻthe competence ofňļ the orphans until they reach a marriageable age. Then if you feel they are capable of sound judgment, return their wealth to them. And do not consume it wastefully and hastily before they grow up ňĻto demand itňļ. If the guardian is well-off, they should not take compensation; but if the guardian is poor, let them take a reasonable provision. When you give orphans back their property, call in witnesses. And sufficient is Allah as a ňĻvigilantňļ Reckoner"
  4,7,"For men there is a share in what their parents and close relatives leave, and for women there is a share in what their parents and close relatives leave‚ÄĒwhether it is little or much. ňĻThese areňļ obligatory shares"
  4,8,"If ňĻnon-inheritingňļ relatives, orphans,¬†or the needy are present at the time of distribution, offer them a ňĻsmallňļ provision from it and speak to them kindly"
  4,9,Let the guardians be as concerned ňĻfor the orphansňļ as they would if they were to ňĻdie andňļ leave ňĻtheir ownňļ helpless children behind. So let them be mindful of Allah and speak equitably
  4,10,"Indeed, those who unjustly consume orphans‚Äô wealth ňĻin factňļ consume nothing but fire into their bellies. And they will be burned in a blazing Hell"
  4,11,"Allah commands you regarding your children: the share of the male will be twice that of the female.¬†If you leave only two ňĻor moreňļ females, their share is two-thirds of the estate. But if there is only one female, her share will be one-half. Each parent is entitled to one-sixth if you leave offspring.¬†But if you are childless and your parents are the only heirs, then your mother will receive one-third.¬†But if you leave siblings, then your mother will receive one-sixth‚ÄĒafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts.¬†ňĻBe fair toňļ your parents and children, as you do not ňĻfullyňļ know who is more beneficial to you.¬†ňĻThis isňļ an obligation from Allah. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,12,"You will inherit half of what your wives leave if they are childless. But if they have children, then ňĻyour share isňļ one-fourth of the estate‚ÄĒafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts. And your wives will inherit one-fourth of what you leave if you are childless. But if you have children, then your wives will receive one-eighth of your estate‚ÄĒafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts. And if a man or a woman leaves neither parents nor children but only a brother or a sister ňĻfrom their mother‚Äôs sideňļ, they will each inherit one-sixth, but if they are more than one, they ňĻallňļ will share one-third of the estate‚ÄĒafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts without harm ňĻto the heirsňļ.¬†ňĻThis isňļ a commandment from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  4,13,"These ňĻentitlementsňļ are the limits set by Allah. Whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger will be admitted into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  4,14,"But whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger and exceeds their limits will be cast into Hell, to stay there forever. And they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  4,15,"ňĻAs forňļ those of your women who commit illegal intercourse‚ÄĒcall four witnesses from among yourselves. If they testify, confine the offenders to their homes until they die or Allah ordains a ňĻdifferentňļ way for them"
  4,16,"And the two among you who commit this sin‚ÄĒdiscipline them. If they repent and mend their ways, relieve them. Surely Allah is ever Accepting of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  4,17,"Allah only accepts the repentance of those who commit evil ignorantly ňĻor recklesslyňļ then repent soon after‚ÄĒAllah will pardon them. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,18,"However, repentance is not accepted from those who knowingly persist in sin until they start dying, and then cry, ‚ÄúNow I repent!‚ÄĚ nor those who die as disbelievers. For them We have prepared a painful punishment"
  4,19,"O believers! It is not permissible for you to inherit women against their will¬†or mistreat them to make them return some of the dowry ňĻas a ransom for divorceňļ‚ÄĒunless they are found guilty of adultery.¬†Treat them fairly. If you happen to dislike them, you may hate something which Allah turns into a great blessing"
  4,20,"If you desire to replace a wife with another and you have given the former ňĻevenňļ a stack of gold ňĻas a dowryňļ, do not take any of it back. Would you ňĻstillňļ take it unjustly and very sinfully"
  4,21,And how could you take it back after having enjoyed each other intimately and she has taken from you a firm commitment
